modelinterfaces

Interface IEntity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IPawn, ISquare
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Dead, Door, Enemy, Entity, Key, Loot, Player, Spell

    public interface IEntity
extends IPawn

    The IEntity interface.

    Implemented by all moving units, so-called entities. It extends IPawn in order to be displayed on a Showboard object.
    Author:
    Ryo SHIINA

      • getDurability

        int getDurability()
        Returns the durability of the entity. If this equals 0, the entity can be destroyed instantly. If this returns a value higher than 0, then it will require a proportional time (counted in frames) before getting destroyed.
        Returns:

      • decrementDurability

        void decrementDurability()
        Decrements the durability of the entity. If its value is already 0, the operation won't happen.
